<li><i>S5</i>&nbsp;:=3D <i>T</i> + <b>5</b></li>
<li><i>D</i>&nbsp;:=3D <i>K</i> + <b>D</b>.</li></ul>
<p><i>K</i> through <i>S5</i> form a nested hierarchy of systems, making up=
 the core of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Normal_modal_logic" t=
itle=3D"Normal modal logic">normal modal logic</a>. But specific rules or s=
ets of rules may be appropriate for specific systems. For example, in <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deontic_logic" title=3D"Deontic logic">=
