 what is natural is also good, by saying that if <i>p</i> is the case, <i>p=
</i> ought to be permitted).
</p><p>The commonly employed system <i>S5</i> simply makes all modal truths=
 necessary. For example, if <i>p</i> is possible, then it is "necessary" th=
at <i>p</i> is possible. Also, if <i>p</i> is necessary, then it is necessa=
ry that <i>p</i> is necessary. Other systems of modal logic have been formu=
lated, in part because <i>S5</i> does not describe every kind of modality o=
