-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:24.363ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \B=
ox (p\to q)\to (\Box p\to \Box q)}"></span>.</li></ul>
<p>It has been questioned whether the epistemic and alethic modalities shou=
ld be considered distinct from each other. The criticism states that there =
is no real difference between "the truth in the world" (alethic) and "the t=
ruth in an individual's mind" (epistemic).<sup id=3D"cite_ref-14" class=3D"=
reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modal_logic#cite_note-1=
4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>14<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</s=
pan></a></sup> An investigation has not found a single language in which al=
ethic and epistemic modalities are formally distinguished, as by the means =
of a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grammatical_mood" title=3D"Gr=
ammatical mood">grammatical mood</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-15" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modal_logic#cite_note-15"><s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>15<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span><=
/a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Temporal_logic">Temporal lo=
