<p>But (1) and <i>K</i> together entail =E2=96=A1<i>Q</i>, which says that =
it ought to be the case that you have stolen a small amount of money. This =
surely is not right, because you ought not to have stolen anything at all. =
And (2) does not work either: If the right representation of "if you have s=
tolen some money it ought to be a small amount" is (2), then the right repr=
